  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia Somaliland Puntland Joint Response (SSPJR)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hardest hit vulnerable pastoralist communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train herders on livestock disease prevention; train community-based animal health workers; distribute water filters/purifiers to vulnerable households; hygiene promotion; rehab communal water points for livestock and household use.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">World Concern, in a joint response, will address humanitarian needs by providing life-saving and life-sustaining assistance to people in need, prioritizing the most vulnerable, by way of the following:
1) Improved immediate access to food and safety nets for people facing severe food insecurity, through unconditional cash transfers;
2) Improved access to safe water, sanitation and hygiene, through distribution of ceramic water filters for household use and targeted hygiene promotion activities and training; and
3) Ensure reliable and sustained access to sufficient, safe water through rehabilitation of strategic water points and establishment of sustainable management structures.</narrative>
  </description>
